Rangers Football Club of Enugu was thrown into mourning yesterday following the death of it’s players in a ghastly auto crash. It was gathered that the players, Ifeanyi George who is a top striker in the senior team and Emmanuel Ogbu who plays in the junior team died while on their way to Lagos on Sunday morning at Abdu, a boundary Community between Delta and Edo states. Sources disclosed that another occupant of the vehicle they were traveling in, identified as a friend to Ifeanyi also died in the accident. The private car they were traveling in was said to have rammed into a truck, killing the three occupants on the spot. In his reaction, the club’s Media/Communication Officer, Norbert Okolie, confirmed the incident . According to him, after visiting the hospital morgue where the bodies are deposited on Sunday, they received the incident with shock. He stated the management on Friday approved a 10-day break for the players following the four weeks suspension of all football activities by the Nigeria Football Federation. Announcing the break, the General Manager of the club, Davidson Owumi had urged the players to be conscious of the health situations around them during the break. Owumi said: “This break is necessitated by the suspension order by the NFF on all football activities in the country and management in its wisdom wants its players to be with their various families in this challenging health period. “It is our belief that the players would maintain a high level of discipline and return after the break stronger to challenge for a top finish in the season.”